question.text: In an energy recycling process, <math> <mrow> <mtext>X</mtext><mtext> </mtext><mtext>g</mtext></mrow> </math> of steam at <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>100 </mn><mo>°</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">C</mi></math> becomes water at <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>100 </mn><mo>°</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">C</mi></math> which converts <math> <mrow> <mtext>Y</mtext><mtext> </mtext><mtext>g</mtext></mrow> </math> of ice at <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>0 </mn><mo>°</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">C</mi></math> into water at <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>100 </mn><mo>°</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">C</mi></math>. The ratio of <math><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">X</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">Y</mi></mrow></mfrac></math> will be (specific heat of water <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mo>=</mo><mn>4200</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant="normal">J</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi>kg</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant="normal">K</mi></math>, specific latent heat of fusion <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mo>=</mo><mn>3.36</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant="normal">J</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi>kg</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>, specific latent heat of vaporization <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mo>=</mo><mn>22.68</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant="normal">J</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi>kg</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>)

solution.text:
Heat loss = Heat gain

m 1 L v = m 2 .L f + m 2 .S.ΔT

X×10-3×22.68×105 =Y×10-3×3.36×105+Y×10-3×4200×100

∴XY=7.5622.68=13
